          <h3>What should I do if I am showing symptoms of COVID-19? </h3>
          <div class="preview-content">
            <p>If you are showing any of the following symptoms:
</p>
<ul>
<li>Loss or decrease in the sense of smell</li>
 	<li>Loss or decrease of the sense of taste</li>
 	<li>Fever – temperature of 100 or higher</li>
 	<li>Cough</li>
 	<li>Congestion</li>
 	<li>Runny nose</li>
 	<li>Sore throat</li>
 	<li>Shortness of breath</li>
 	<li>Flu-like body aches</li>
</ul>
Call 847-HEALTH9 (847-432-5849) or your local doctor. If you are a NorthShore patient, you can also log onto <a href="https://www.northshoreconnect.org/mychart/">NorthShore Connect</a> to be screened.<p>
          </p>
</div>
        </li>
              <li class="preview">
          <h3>Have there been any reported or confirmed cases of COVID-19 in Glenview or Northbrook?</h3>
          <div class="preview-content">
            <p>The Cook County Department of Public Health has a <a href="https://ccdphcd.shinyapps.io/covid19/">heat map</a> on their website that details how many cases there are by community. Please note that only confirmed cases are listed on the CCDPH site.</p>
<p>
          </p>
</div>
        </li>
              <li class="preview">
          <h3>Where can I go to receive financial assistance or support?</h3>
          <div class="preview-content">
            <p>Northfield Township residents in need of emergency financial assistance can call the Township office (847-724-8300) during business hours.</p>
<p>
          </p>
</div>
        </li>
              <li class="preview">
          <h3>Can my kids or teens play at the parks or playgrounds?</h3>
          <div class="preview-content">
            <p>Following Governor Pritzker’s extension of the Stay At Home Order through the end of April, the Northbrook Village President issued an Order that states that no person can use a public building, place, property, or street for close-contact group sports, activities that involve shared sports equipment, or for group exercise programs, which includes parks and playgrounds.  The Village of Glenview urges residents to refrain from congregating in parks and playgrounds.</p>
<p>
          </p>
</div>
        </li>
          </ul>
